features: VINTAGE WALL ART DECOR: Titled "Stilleven met gitaar en rozen", this oil painting is the work of the 19th-century Dutch flower painter Margaretha Roosenboom, known for her still lives of flowers and fruit. The composition of the image and the use of light and shadow create a harmonious balance, the flowers and guitars complement each other in the overall arrangement, and the brown and green tones are simply classical and exquisite.

SPICE UP YOUR WALL: The LITIVY canvas wall art collection has been carefully selected to reflect the unique styles and themes of different eras, from classic medieval to Renaissance Art Deco. The timeless appeal of these wall art adds a touch of elegance and nostalgia to any space, making it a great choice for art lovers and fans of classic paintings. Provide a great room decor for your living room, bedroom, bathroom, home bar, office, kitchen, dining room and more.

PREMIUM MATERIALS: This vintage oil painting is printed on canvas wrapped in wood fiberboard and finished with a clear gel medium to keep it water-resistant, making the color vibrant and long-lasting. High quality canvas material has great visual and tactile effects. Classic wall art paintings will add light and life to your room and maintain its beauty for many years.

EASY TO HANG: Framed canvas farmhouse wall art is a lightweight piece that's super easy to hang! Comes with hooks for easy hanging and wipes gently with a soft cloth to keep it looking its best. You don’t need to drill many holes in the wall to maintain it. No assembly required! Or just place it on a shelf or table.

GREAT GIFT IDEA: This framed vintage wall art decoration is perfect for year-round decoration and makes a great gift for a loved one on any special occasion. Each piece is carefully selected to evoke emotion and spark conversation. The wall oil paintings also make a wonderful wedding gifts, housewarming gifts, anniversary gifts, bridal shower gifts for couples, engagement party gifts, and Valentine's gifts.

reviews.reviewText: Beautiful framed artwork does not have to be expensive - this framed canvas (Brown-Garden) is beautiful and just the touch I was looking for in my small home office. The colors seem very true to what is shown online, and the piece is light-weight and very easy to hang.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Adhesive holding the picture failed
reviews.reviewText: This arrived with the picture detached from the frame - the adhesive evidently failed. It may be a quality control issue, or it may be a poor choice of how to mount the picture. I received this as a "free" item, so I'll affix the picture properly and make the repair. Had I purchased it directly, it would've been returned.APPEARANCE: The picture looks fine. It's a print on canvas, adhered to a board that (I think at one point at least) attaches onto the frame. The print is ONLY the front of the board, so the tiny sliver of edge you see on the edge of the picture where it's "floating" in the frame is wood. There are other similar products on here that arrived with the printed canvas wrapped all the way around the board, so this picture looks less professional than those.CONSTRUCTION: The frame is lightweight; I think it's a veneered pressed-wood. the print is cut exactly to size and smoothly adhered to the front of a board. The board is then glued to the frame. Mine arrived with the frame glue unstuck. It doesn't look difficult to repair, if you have the patience to re-glue and steady enough hands to get it centered in the frame. It comes with two mounting hooks to push into the wall. The back of the frame is wide enough for some hook and loop strips or perhaps some Command strips to hold it up.NOTE: the exterior dimensions are a little shy of what's advertised at 11 13/16" x 15 3/4". The print itself is smaller than that at 11 1/8" x 15 1/8".

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A unique addition to home gallery
reviews.reviewText: This "brown-rose" painting is a very pleasing addition to my art gallery. The colors are warm, but not too dark (and the staircase where this is has poor lighting). I love the style of the canvas inset into the wood frame and how easy it was to install. It came packaged well and with all the hardware needed to hang it. I don't have any complaints!
